In the current screen image, the PDF file has been opened in the Mozilla Firefox browser. Users may want to scroll through the rest of the content, especially if the PDF document has more than one page. To view more content of the PDF file, perform the following actions:```json
[
    {"action_type": "MouseAction", "mouse_action_type": "scroll_down", "scroll_repeat": 10}
]
```This operation command will simulate the scroll wheel to scroll down. It is assumed that a certain amount of content will be scrolled every time the action is repeated` Scroll_ The number of repeat 'can be adjusted according to the actual situation to view more content or reach a specific part of the document.
